# xlsx_to_csv_consolidator

A simple Python tool to consolidate multiple `.xlsx` files from a folder (and subfolders) into a single `.csv` file.

## ✨ Features

- Recursively scans a folder for `.xlsx` files
- Consolidates all of them into a single `DataFrame` via Pandas
- Exports the result as a single `.csv`
- Configurable paths via environment variables (no sensitive data exposed)

## 🛠️ Technologies

- Python 3.13.5
- [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/)
- [python-dotenv](https://pypi.org/project/python-dotenv/)

## 🚀 How to use

### 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/sucrilos_kelogs/xlsx_to_csv_consolidator.git
cd xlsx_to_csv_consolidator

### 2. Install dependencies
pip install pandas python-dotenv

### 3. Configure environment variables
Copy the example file and fill in your paths:
cp .env.example .env

Edit the `.env`:
SOURCE_FOLDER=C:\path\to\your\source\folder
OUTPUT_FILE=C:\path\to\your\output\file.csv

### 4. Run
python consolidator.py

## ⚠️ Known limitations

- Does not use a database (e.g. DuckDB), so it **cannot detect changes** in already-processed files — only the addition of new files.
- All `.xlsx` files must have a compatible column structure for the concatenation to work correctly.

## 📁 Project structure

xlsx_to_csv_consolidator/
├── consolidator.py    # Main script
├── .env.example       # Configuration template
├── .gitignore         # Ignores .env and generated files
└── README.md

